   <concept id="FAR_9_109_4" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">9.109-4</ph> Certification by the
offeror.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="id188S9000L80" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li id="id188S9400V6B" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d572e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> In order to
be eligible for contract award, an offeror is required to—</p>
               <ol id="id188S9205082" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d572e16">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                     </p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d572e21">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Certify that it does not engage
and has not engaged in any activity that contributed to or was a
significant factor in the President's or Secretary of State's determination
that a foreign country is in violation of its obligations undertaken
in any arms control, nonproliferation, or disarmament agreement
to which the United States is a party, or is not adhering to its
arms control, nonproliferation, or disarmament commitments in which
the United States is a participating state. The determinations are
described in the most recent unclassified annual report provided
to Congress pursuant to section 403 of the Arms Control and Disarmament
Act (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title22-section2593a&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">22 U.S.C. 2593a</xref>).
The report is available at 
                              <xref href="https://www.state.gov/bureaus-offices/under-secretary-for-arms-control-and-international-security-affairs/bureau-of-arms-control-verification-and-compliance/"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">https://www.state.gov/bureaus-offices/under-secretary-for-arms-control-and-international-security-affairs/bureau-of-arms-control-verification-and-compliance/</xref>;
and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d572e32">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Similarly
certify with regard to any entity owned or controlled by the offeror;
or</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d572e37">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Provide
with its offer information that the President of the United States
has–</p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d572e43">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Waived
application under <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title22-section2593e&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">22 U.S.C. 2593e</xref>(d)
or (e); or</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d572e51">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Determined
under <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title22-section2593e&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">22 U.S.C. 2593e</xref>(g)(2)
that the entity has ceased all activities for which measures were imposed
under <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title22-section2593e&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">22 U.S.C. 2593e</xref>(b).</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d572e62">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> If certifying
in accordance with <xref href="52.209-13.dita#FAR_52_209_13"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.209-13</xref>(b)(1), the Offeror
is required to submit the certification with the offer. It is not
included in the annual representations and certifications in the
System for Award Management.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d572e70">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> The contracting
officer may rely on an offeror's certification unless the contracting
officer has reason to question the certification.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d572e75">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph "/>Upon
the determination of a false certification under <xref href="52.209-13.dita#FAR_52_209_13"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.209-13</xref>,
an offeror will be subject to such remedies as suspension or debarment
under subpart <xref href="Subpart_9.4.dita#FAR_Subpart_9_4"
                        base="i1115147"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">9.4</xref> shall
be for a period of not less than 2 years, inclusive of any suspension
period, if suspension precedes a debarment (see <xref href="9.406-4.dita#FAR_9_406_4"
                        base="i1115302"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">9.406-4</xref>(a)(1)(iii) and
(a)(2)).
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
